# Platform Architecture Rules

## Intent
Define the structural rules for the rewrite product so chat and plugin systems remain modular, safe, and maintainable.

## Mandatory
- Treat chat as the core product surface; all service capabilities are invoked as plugin actions or commands.
- Keep plugin execution behind a centralized policy and permission layer.
- Use shared contracts for web/mobile/backend payloads and command schemas.
- Isolate plugin domains to avoid cross-service coupling and unintended data sharing.
- Enforce explicit ownership for each bounded context and service.

## Integration Rules
- No plugin may directly bypass core chat policy middleware.
- No plugin may access another plugin's sensitive storage without an approved shared contract.
- Introduce adapters at boundaries when integrating legacy concepts.

## Release Blockers
- New service path that is not represented as a plugin contract.
- Feature architecture that bypasses centralized auth, policy, or audit hooks.